sequenceDiagram
  %% Diagram 36: JWT, Refresh Token, and MFA Lifecycle

  autonumber
  actor U as User
  participant A as Auth API
  participant M as MFA Verifier
  participant T as Token Service
  participant S as Session Store

  U->>A: POST /api/auth/login (credentials)
  A->>A: Verify credentials
  alt MFA required
    A->>M: Challenge TOTP
    M-->>A: MFA result
    alt MFA failed
      A-->>U: 401 Unauthorized
    else MFA passed
      A->>T: Issue access (15m) + refresh
      T-->>A: Tokens
      A->>S: Persist refresh token family
      A-->>U: Login success
    end
  else MFA not required
    A->>T: Issue access (15m) + refresh
    T-->>A: Tokens
    A->>S: Persist refresh token family
    A-->>U: Login success
  end

  U->>A: Access token expires after 15m
  U->>A: POST /api/auth/refresh (refresh token)
  A->>S: Validate refresh family and replay status
  A->>T: Rotate refresh token and issue new access
  alt Refresh valid
    T-->>A: New access + refresh
    A->>S: Invalidate old refresh token
    A-->>U: Rotated token pair
  else Refresh invalid or expired
    A-->>U: Re-authentication required
  end
